@C sim-scale-up-INDIRECT-INFERENCE :: meta [4!]
  → "★★★ INDIRECT INFERENCE from energy-density finite-size effect:"
  → ""
  → "  The 6.3× drop in energy density (13.2 → 2.1) from σ²=64 to σ²=4096"
  → "  suggests that ANY observable that depends on per-cell energy at"
  → "  σ²=64 is operating in a finite-size regime."
  → ""
  → "  Implications for 46-iter cascade findings (HYPOTHESIS, not test):"
  → "  ★ axis-14 (4p(1-p) entropy of state distribution): if state values"
  → "      are bounded by SCALE_BASE=1000 and L=4 init has sharp central"
  → "      peak, axis-14 is dominated by center-vs-boundary contrast at"
  → "      σ²=64 — would FLATTEN at σ²>=512 (more bulk cells)"
  → "  ★ axis-15 (Lorentz energy-drift): drift ∝ Δ(energy)/tick. At σ²=64"
  → "      tick perturbation (tick % 31) is order ~30 vs energy ~13/cell;"
  → "      perturbation/energy ratio ~2.3. At σ²=4096, ratio ~14 — drift"
  → "      becomes RELATIVELY STRONGER per cell, may invert sign of"
  → "      axis-14 × axis-15 correlation"
  → "  ★ axis-13 (D=2 << D=3 << D=6 ranking): NOT INFERABLE from this"
  → "      module — different lattice dimensionalities (D=2,3,6) not"
  → "      represented in scale_universe.hexa (T³ only = D=3)"
  → ""
  → "  These are HYPOTHESES generated by scale-up data, not measurements."
  → "  Genuine test requires module extension (Stage 5 follow-up)."

